FILE: Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane says cleaning up corruption and fraudulent activities in the province will be his guiding priority. EAST LONDON - ANC Eastern Cape PTT Convener, Oscar Mabuyane says any issues of vote-buying should be formally reported so they can be properly dealt with. Mabuyane, who is campaigning to retain his position, says he is not in it for the money. Meanwhile, Mabuyane has called for calm ahead of the province’s elective conference. READ: ANC Eastern Cape conference gets underway Mabuyane says this weekend's gathering should not be treated as a battlefield. He has pleading with party members to avoid sending mixed messages to the public. Mabuyane will be going toe to toe with Babalo Madikizela in a battle over the top spot.